The paper also discusses randomized and parallel algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of concentration results and information theory techniques indicates that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the use of maximal independent sets, which is a topic in machine learning and graph theory, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
